Constant :- Remains same irrespect of who is using. Ex. 3, 4, etc.
Variable :- can be change by user. Ex. a, b, x, y, etc.
variables name can not start with any number or any special characters excluding underscore( _ ).
There are many different types of data types in C++ .
Integer types :- int, short, long, unsigned int, etc.
Floating-point types :- float, double
Character type :- char, wchar_t
Boolean type: bool
User-defined types: struct, class, enum, etc
Declaring a variable :-
        data type  variable name ;
        Example:  int rollno;
